label start:
    call create_my_quests

    jump sun_speech

    label sun_speech:
        s_unknown "They say our ancestors are suffering."
        show start bg with fade
        s sitting "It's been nearly three moons since the moonpool ran dry."
        s "By now, I think it's safe to say it's basically no more than a dusty pit."
        s rising "Since then, I think all of us have seen things that defy description."
        s standing "Kits, shriveled to husks like leaves on the vine."
        s "Elders ravaged by sickness."
        s "The bitter cold. The stench of death."
        s sitting "And, of course, the unending hunger."
        s "A whole leaf-bare without so much as a shrew's tail for ThunderClan to eat."
        s rising "Leadership has failed us. So has the warrior code."
        s "Our Clan has been abandoned by any sense of logic or reason."
        s sitting "... And now, to top it all off, my mate is dead."
        show dapplefeather bg with fade
        s_unknown "My Dapplefeather. Forty-two moons old."
        s_unknown "Our first litter of kits was born just five days ago."
        s_unknown "She died before they could even get their eyes open."
        s_unknown "Our kits will grow up with no recollection of their mother's face."
        hide dapplefeather bg
        s "..."
        s rising "She was sick for a good while. Weakened by the hunger."
        s "When I first heard the news she passed, all I could do was wonder:"
        s standing "Is she really in StarClan, now?"
        s "Has her suffering ended? Has she reached any kind of peace?"
        s sitting "... Or, are our warrior ancestors all starving up there, too?"
        scene sunset clouds with fade
        s_unknown "To my Dapplefeather, if you can hear me, I have only this to say:"
        s_unknown "I hope you're hurting."
        s_unknown "I hope you feel your Clanmates' agony."
        s_unknown "I hope the hunger never goes away."
        s_unknown "Because, if it does ..."
        s_unknown "If it's true that, after all these moons, StarClan is still lush and warm and overflowing with prey ..."
        s_unknown "Then it means that, all this time, they could've been helping us."
        s_unknown "They've just chosen not to."
        s_unknown "And, if that's the case, then I won't stop until every last speck of light is clawed from the sky, myself."
        s_unknown "I hope none of us ever forgets this feeling."
        s_unknown "The hunger and the cold. I hope they never go away."
        s_unknown "StarClan, what a waste."
        s_unknown "What a collosal waste ..."
        s_unknown "..."
        scene black with fade